lecture 2 - ethics
theories

deontological theory -
  do the right thing,
  do it because its right to do
  don't do the wrong thing

utilitarian vs deontological
ut: happiness is the only thing that matters

contractarianism - ethic based on the contract
come together with the interest of mutual interests
moral behaviour as a type of cooperation that, in the long run, benefits everyone

problem of impartiality:
2 aspects - impartiality and universality

